# Monorepo conventions

## Language

All files under `packages/` and `apps/` must be in **English** (see `english-only` rule).

## Dependencies

- Add deps in the specific package `package.json`, not root (except shared dev tools)
- Workspace: `"workspace:*"` for internal packages
- Peer deps: React, Angular, Next, Express — in UI/server packages

## Build (tsup + TypeScript 7 declarations)

- Entry in `tsup.config.ts`, output in `dist/` (gitignored)
- `clean: !process.argv.includes("--watch")` — watch must not wipe dist (avoids monorepo races)
- `dts: false` in tsup — bundle JS only; emit `.d.ts` with `scripts/emit-package-dts.mjs` (native `tsc`, TypeScript 7)
- Library packages declare `@typescript/native` only; `typescript` (Compiler API alias) stays on root and `demo-next` until TS 7.1 tooling support

## Turbo

- `build` depends on `^build` (dependencies first)
- Library `dev`: `dependsOn: ["^build", "build"]`
- `lint` / `typecheck` / `test` depend on `^build`

## New feature order

1. `core` (+ tests) → 2. `server` (+ tests) → 3. UI (`react`/`angular`) → 4. `demo-next`
2. Finish with: `pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm build`

## Style

- Minimal diff, English in code and public APIs
- Public API changes → update README / CHANGELOG
